      • initialize

        public void initialize​(java.net.URL url,
                       java.util.ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
        Initializes the modify part page. Checks to see if the selected part to modify is in-house or outsourced and changes the page to display appropriately. Sets the values of the text boxes to the values assigned to the part when it was created.
        Specified by:
        initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable
        Parameters:
        url - The location used to resolve relative paths for the root object, or null if the location is not known.
        resourceBundle - The resources used to localize the root object, or null if the root object was not localized.

      • saveClicked

        public void saveClicked​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
                 throws java.io.IOException
        Method is called when the save button is pressed. Saves the data user inputs into the modify part page. Creates a new part object and saves it to inventory while keeping the same unique ID. Deletes the old part from inventory. Checks for valid input into text fields and returns user to the main screen when save is successful.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - Save button clicked
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Catches invalid data entry errors
